condition.narrative: Develop a policy and take proper regulatory and other actions for the protection of registered property rights, in a manneracceptable to the Association.
Submission to Parliament a revised law on urban management.

title.narrative: Cities in which New Street Addressing & Building Numbering System Implemented

comment.narrative: As of restructuring
Bidding documents for additional street addressing were submitted on December 10, leaving insufficient time to proceed. Projecttarget has already been met.

title.narrative: Investment in priority infrastructure and services completed

comment.narrative: Baseline as of project restructuring.
Assumes completion of 4 subprojects at $800,000 equivalent of which 50% financed by IBRD.
All four municipal investment projects have been completed and handed over and have satisfactorily completed their performanceperiod.
Baseline as of project restructuring.
Target date revised.(Value represents drainage pumping stations that will be rehabilitated).
The work in Velipoja will be completed by mid-November, 2013. The target date for Cas and Tale has been extended to May 2014.

title.narrative: Water testing equipment installed and in use in Shkodra

comment.narrative: Baseline as of project restructuring.
This activity has not been implemented, so far, due to the inability of the Shkodra Water Supply Utility to provide the list andspecifications for the related equipment
Baseline as of project restructuring.
Target date revised. (Value represents pumping stations that will be rehabilitated).
Works for two pumping stations was completed in December 2012. Works on Trush -- the third station -- is about 55% complete, andthe revised date of completion is December 15, 2013.

title.narrative: Agricultural land protected by rehabilitated drainage pumps

comment.narrative: Baseline begins at date of restructuring
Target date revised. (Value is in hectares of agricultural land).
The work in Velipoja will be completed by the end of November 2013. The target date for Cas and Tale has been extended to May 2014.
Baseline is project restructuring date.
Completed.

title.narrative: Number of municipalities that complete the regulatory plans.

comment.narrative: All 8 Territorial Plans have been completed.
All 8 Territorial Plans prepared under the project have been completed and accepted by the National Territorial Planning Agency.

title.narrative: Number of titles issued in urban and rural areas.

comment.narrative: Target date revised.

Continued progress in finalizing titles.26% increase since last ISR. 40% achievement vs. overall target.Note: The last ISRstated the actual figure as 12,783,800 when it should have been 127,838.00 titles.
Target date revised.
Roll-out in progress for additional five offices.The remaining 5 offices have local servers but have not been connected to thecentral server yet. This is expected to be completed by the next mission.

title.narrative: Number of municipalities that completed interim reforms and qualified for the first phase of investments

comment.narrative: Target achieved.

title.narrative: Number of municipalities that received training in procurement and financial management

comment.narrative: Target achieved.

title.narrative: Number of local offices that received training.

comment.narrative: Target date revised.
Training coincides with the roll-out of the IT system, and will be completed alongside the roll-out in the remaining 5 offices.

title.narrative: Reduction in time to register property transaction

comment.narrative: Target is 5 days as per the 2011 Restructuring Paper.

This data from the new IT system. The value of the indicator has increased from 9.0 to 9.8 days because it reflects data fromTirana and 4 additional district offices, and, therefore, is more representative.

title.narrative: Customer satisfation of the IPRO is improved (on a scale from "Very Poor, Poor, Average, Good, Very Good, and Excellent") to the level of "Very Good"

comment.narrative: Target date is revised.
Based on the 2012 customer satisfaction survey.
